result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeremiah O Kimbrough was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Jeremiah O Kimbrough in court, in custody, with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.   Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to counts 3,4 and 5. Counts 1, 2, 6 and 7 are dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following: AS TO CTS. 3 AND 4

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 1/2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT  
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 1/2  YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  4 YEAR(S); concurrent with each other, but consecutive to count 5

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  any co-actors, victims or their residences
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*2005 Dodge Van Vin #2V4GP44L55R221468 to be forfeited

RESTITUTION IS SET AT "0"
 
COURT COSTS:  $268.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
